ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Add the SSH Key to Your GitHub Account
Go to GitHub SSH Keys
Title: My Dev Machine or any name
Key: Paste the copied public key
Click Add SSH Key


ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Update Your Git Remote to Use SSH
Run this in your project directory:
bash
CopyEdit
